      <description>
        
        
        &lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minikube&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;minikube delete &amp;ndash;profile &lt;profilename&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;minikube ip&lt;/code&gt;  gives the ip of minikube&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ping command&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ping command uses ICMP (Internet Control Message Protocol), and not TCP/UDP hence cannot ping a particular host&amp;rsquo;s port.sends an ICMP echo request to the target host
and waits for ICMP echo reply.The time parameter defines the total time taken to send an ICMP request to the target and the reply back to the source target,hence the
name Round Trip Time(RTT), hencethe latency&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;dig: Domain Information Groper&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;collects data about Domain Name Servers like DNS records&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;dig +short blog.vinay.im&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;where blog.vinay.im is the target&amp;rsquo;s domain name&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;dig blog.vinay.im&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;code-block relative mt-6 first:mt-0 group/code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;
